RESTIC RESTORE PROCEDURE — {{ ansible_hostname | default('srfaudio') }} Synology NAS
Generated by Ansible role synology_restic_backup on {{ ansible_date_time.iso8601 | default('(see 1Password item for creation date)') }}
================================================================================

This file documents every step required to restore data from the Hetzner
Storage Box restic repository to a clean machine. It is intentionally
self-contained — you do not need access to the Ansible repository to use it.

REPOSITORY DETAILS
------------------
  Backend:          SFTP (Hetzner Storage Box)
  Storage Box host: {{ synology_restic_backup_storagebox_host }}
  Storage Box user: {{ synology_restic_backup_storagebox_user }}
  SFTP port:        {{ synology_restic_backup_storagebox_port }}
  Repository path:  {{ synology_restic_backup_storagebox_repo_path }}
                    (relative to Storage Box home directory)
  Full restic URL:  sftp:storagebox:{{ synology_restic_backup_storagebox_repo_path }}

  Snapshot tag:     {{ synology_restic_backup_snapshot_tag }}
  Backup paths:
{% for path in synology_restic_backup_backup_paths %}
    - {{ path }}
{% endfor %}

SECRETS (retrieve from 1Password)
----------------------------------
  Vault:                    {{ synology_restic_backup_op_vault }}
  Restic password item:     {{ synology_restic_backup_op_restic_repo_item }}
    Field:                  {{ synology_restic_backup_op_restic_repo_password_field }}
  Storage Box SSH key item: {{ synology_restic_backup_op_storagebox_ssh_key_item }}
    Field:                  {{ synology_restic_backup_op_storagebox_ssh_key_field }}

STEP 1 — Install restic on the restore machine
-----------------------------------------------
Download the official binary for your platform from:
  https://github.com/restic/restic/releases/tag/v{{ synology_restic_backup_restic_version }}

Verify the SHA256 checksum before proceeding:
  sha256sum restic_*_linux_amd64.bz2
  # compare against the SHA256SUMS file at the same release URL

Extract and install:
  bzip2 -d restic_{{ synology_restic_backup_restic_version }}_linux_amd64.bz2
  chmod 755 restic_{{ synology_restic_backup_restic_version }}_linux_amd64
  mv restic_{{ synology_restic_backup_restic_version }}_linux_amd64 /usr/local/bin/restic

STEP 2 — Configure SSH for the Storage Box
-------------------------------------------
Retrieve the Storage Box SSH private key from 1Password:
  op read "op://{{ synology_restic_backup_op_vault }}/{{ synology_restic_backup_op_storagebox_ssh_key_item }}/{{ synology_restic_backup_op_storagebox_ssh_key_field }}" \
      --out-file ~/.ssh/storagebox-key
  chmod 400 ~/.ssh/storagebox-key

Add the following block to ~/.ssh/config (create the file if it does not exist):

  Host storagebox
      HostName {{ synology_restic_backup_storagebox_host }}
      User {{ synology_restic_backup_storagebox_user }}
      Port {{ synology_restic_backup_storagebox_port }}
      IdentityFile ~/.ssh/storagebox-key
      IdentitiesOnly yes
      StrictHostKeyChecking accept-new

Test the SSH connection:
  ssh storagebox

STEP 3 — Set the required environment variables
-------------------------------------------------
Retrieve the restic repository password from 1Password:
  export RESTIC_PASSWORD
  RESTIC_PASSWORD=$(op read "op://{{ synology_restic_backup_op_vault }}/{{ synology_restic_backup_op_restic_repo_item }}/{{ synology_restic_backup_op_restic_repo_password_field }}")

  export RESTIC_REPOSITORY="sftp:storagebox:{{ synology_restic_backup_storagebox_repo_path }}"

STEP 4 — List snapshots
------------------------
  restic snapshots --tag {{ synology_restic_backup_snapshot_tag }}

  To list all snapshots regardless of tag:
  restic snapshots

STEP 5 — Restore data
----------------------
OPTION A — Restore a specific snapshot to a directory:
  restic restore <SNAPSHOT_ID> --target /restore

  The snapshot ID is shown in the output of "restic snapshots". Use "latest"
  to restore the most recent snapshot:
  restic restore latest --target /restore

OPTION B — Restore a specific subdirectory from the latest snapshot:
  restic restore latest \
      --target /restore \
      --include "{{ synology_restic_backup_backup_paths | first }}/photo"

OPTION C — Mount the repository as a FUSE filesystem (Linux only):
  mkdir /mnt/restic
  restic mount /mnt/restic
  # Browse files under /mnt/restic/snapshots/<snapshot-id>/
  # Copy what you need, then:
  fusermount -u /mnt/restic

STEP 6 — Verify restored data
------------------------------
  # Check file counts and sizes match expectations
{% for path in synology_restic_backup_backup_paths %}
  du -sh /restore{{ path }}
{% endfor %}

  # Spot-check a specific directory
  ls -la /restore{{ synology_restic_backup_backup_paths | first }}/

